+---
+name: core-trail-architecture
+description: Per-ETF trailing-stop state for the core sleeve — DB-canonical since Phase 1b #116 (PR #139). The `core_trail` table in `data/trading.db` is the source of truth; `memory/CORE-TRAIL.md` is a rendered view produced on demand by `python3 -m scripts.core_trail render`. The pure-function ratchet (`scripts.core_trail.TrailState` + `update_trail` + `breach_status`) is preserved verbatim from pre-#116 — only the I/O layer changed. Use this skill whenever debugging a trail update, a missing/extra row in `core_trail`, a render that doesn't match the committed markdown, an operator who hand-edited the markdown and lost their changes, or when adding a new core ETF. Covers: the v5 schema (10 inputs-only columns, derived `stop`/`status` recomputed at render time); the guarded one-time `_migrate_core_trail_to_v5(conn)` helper (the DROP must NEVER live in `_SCHEMA_SQL` — `executescript()` runs that on every reopen and would wipe data; `test_core_trail_v4_to_v5_migration_is_idempotent` is the regression guard); the `update_state` orchestrator's invariants (ATH ratchets up only; `ath_close_date` advances ONLY when `ath_close` advances; `breach_date` set on transition into breached and preserved on subsequent breached observations; `re_entry_watch` ALWAYS preserved from existing row — operator-managed, never auto-cleared; `currency` carried forward from existing row or inferred via `_infer_currency(symbol)`); the renderer template (locked: H1 + DB-canonical intro + Per-ETF format schema example + per-symbol H2 blocks ORDER BY symbol + Behavior block); the `update` and `render` CLI subcommands; the `CORE_TRAIL_DB` and `CORE_TRAIL_MARKDOWN` env-var overrides (used by the autouse conftest fixture); the dashboard read path (`dashboard/api/app/data/memory_files.py:read_core_trail()` queries DB and computes derived fields via the canonical `breach_status`); and the dual-writer model (the slash command `.claude/commands/check-triggers.md` step 0 + the cloud routine `routines/check-triggers-daily.md` step 3 both call `python3 -m scripts.core_trail update ...` — manual claude.ai prompt re-sync is required after any repo change to the routine prompt block, per memory `project_cloud_routine_config_drift`). Trigger phrases: 'core_trail', 'CORE-TRAIL.md', 'trailing stop', 'core trail', 'trail state', 'ath_close', 'breach_date', 're_entry_watch', '/check-triggers', 'update_state', 'render core trail', 'backfill_core_trail', 'CORE_TRAIL_DB', '_migrate_core_trail_to_v5'.
+---
+
+# Core Trail Architecture (DB-canonical, since Phase 1b #116)
+
+> Phase 1b #116 (PR #139) migrated `memory/CORE-TRAIL.md` from
+> agent-prose-managed canonical markdown to a DB-canonical `core_trail`
+> table. Mirrors Phase 1a (PR #137) literally with one deliberate
+> deviation in step 5 (the prose rewire). Design spec:
+> `docs/superpowers/specs/2026-05-24-phase-1b-core-trail-design.md`.
+
+## Split (do not violate)
+
+- **`scripts/core_trail.py` — extends the pure-function ratchet with DB
+  I/O + render-on-demand.** Spec mandates one module: pure fns
+  (`TrailState`, `update_trail`, `breach_status`) + DB I/O (`read_state`,
+  `write_state`, `update_state`) + render (`render`, `render_to`) + CLI
+  (`update`, `render` subcommands). The pure fns are preserved
+  byte-identical; only the I/O layer is new.
+- **`scripts/db.py:_migrate_core_trail_to_v5(conn)` — one-time guarded
+  rebuild.** Runs in `connect()` after `executescript(_SCHEMA_SQL)`;
+  detects v4 by the `breached` column; DROPs+CREATEs to v5. **The DROP
+  must NEVER live inside `_SCHEMA_SQL`** — `executescript()` runs that on
+  every reopen, which would wipe data on every connect.
+  `tests/test_db.py::test_core_trail_v4_to_v5_migration_is_idempotent`
+  is the regression guard (seeds v4 → connects → inserts row → closes →
+  reconnects → asserts row survived).
+- **`scripts/backfill_core_trail.py` — one-shot, idempotent markdown →
+  DB seed.** Existing-symbol rows are reported as `unchanged`, never
+  updated. Hand-edited DB rows are protected. Lives in repo as audit
+  trail. Required date fields (`ath_close_date`, `last_observed_date`)
+  must be populated; missing → `ValueError` (guards future per-symbol
+  half-populated YAML blocks).
+- **`dashboard/api/app/data/memory_files.py:read_core_trail()` — reads
+  DB, computes derived fields.** `try/finally conn.close()` (sqlite3
+  `with conn:` is transaction-context, NOT close). `stop` and `status`
+  computed via canonical `scripts.core_trail.breach_status` — no
+  duplicated ratchet logic in dashboard layer.
+
+## v5 schema (10 inputs-only columns)
+
+```sql
+symbol TEXT PRIMARY KEY
+ath_close REAL NOT NULL                  -- native currency
+ath_close_date TEXT NOT NULL             -- 'YYYY-MM-DD'
+last_observed REAL NOT NULL
+last_observed_date TEXT NOT NULL
+trail_pct REAL NOT NULL
+breach_date TEXT                         -- NULL = not breached
+re_entry_watch INTEGER NOT NULL DEFAULT 0
+currency TEXT NOT NULL                   -- 'EUR', 'USD', ...
+updated_at TEXT NOT NULL
+```
+
+`stop = ath_close * (1 - trail_pct/100)` and `status ∈ {ok, approaching,
+breached}` are **derived at render time** — they are NOT stored. This
+diverges from Phase 1a's `reserve_ledger` (which stores `balance_after`
+as audit denormalization for an append-only ledger). `core_trail` is
+single-row-per-symbol mutable; no audit reason to denormalize.
+
+## `update_state` orchestrator invariants
+
+`scripts.core_trail.update_state(conn, *, symbol, current_close,
+observed_date, trail_pct, currency=None) -> CoreTrailRow`:
+
+| Invariant | Why |
+|---|---|
+| Fresh symbol → `current_close` seeds both `ath_close` and `last_observed`; both date fields = `observed_date`; `re_entry_watch=False`; `currency = currency or _infer_currency(symbol)` | First observation has no prior state |
+| Existing row → applies pure-fn `update_trail` against prior state | Preserves ratchet semantics |
+| `ath_close_date` advances ONLY when `new.ath_close > existing.ath_close` | The ATH date is the date the high was set, not the date of the latest observation |
+| `breach_date = existing.breach_date or observed_date` when status == `breached`; preserved otherwise | Records the FIRST breach date; subsequent breached closes don't overwrite |
+| `re_entry_watch` ALWAYS carried from existing row | Operator-managed flag; never auto-set or auto-cleared by `update_state`. Operator flips it via direct DB UPDATE or another `update` call |
+| `currency = currency or existing.currency` | Carried forward; inferred only on fresh seed |
+| Invalid `trail_pct` (≤0 or >100) → `ValueError` from `update_trail` | Pure-fn validation propagates |
+
+## Renderer template (locked, byte-identical contract)
+
+`scripts.core_trail.render(conn) -> str` produces the canonical on-disk
+form of `memory/CORE-TRAIL.md`. Structure:
+
+```
+# Core ETF Trailing Stop -- current state
+
+<DB-canonical intro paragraph>
+
+## Per-ETF format
+<yaml schema example with comments on derived fields>
+
+## {SYMBOL}                <- one block per row, ORDER BY symbol
+<yaml block with all 10 inputs + derived stop/status>
+
+## Behavior
+<static behavior prose, refers to `python3 -m scripts.core_trail update ...`>
+```
+
+Numeric formatting: `{:.2f}` for prices (note `158.06 * 0.80 = 126.448
+→ 126.45` due to `:.2f` rounding — the live trigger check uses the
+unrounded float internally), `{:g}` for `trail_pct`, lowercase
+`true`/`false` for booleans, literal `null` for missing `breach_date`.
+Trailing newline at EOF. LF line endings (`render_to` uses
+`newline="\n"`).
+
+`tests/test_core_trail_render.py::test_render_byte_identical_to_committed_markdown`
+pins the contract: `render(conn)` output IS `memory/CORE-TRAIL.md`
+byte-for-byte. The raw-bytes guard (`assert b"\r\n" not in raw`) defeats
+Windows universal-newline silent normalization.
+
+## CLI surface
+
+```bash
+# Write trail state for one observation (writes DB row + re-renders markdown
+# + prints new-state JSON on stdout):
+python3 -m scripts.core_trail update \
+    --symbol VWCE.DE --close 157.98 --date 2026-05-07 --trail-pct 20 \
+    [--currency EUR]
+
+# Render current DB state to markdown:
+python3 -m scripts.core_trail render             # stdout
+python3 -m scripts.core_trail render --write     # writes memory/CORE-TRAIL.md
+
+# One-shot backfill from markdown (operator runs once post-merge):
+python3 -m scripts.backfill_core_trail [--symbol SYM] [--dry-run]
+```
+
+The `update` CLI's stdout JSON shape (for the agent's report path in
+`/check-triggers`):
+
+```json
+{"symbol": "VWCE.DE", "ath_close": 157.98, "ath_close_date": "2026-05-07",
+ "stop": 126.45, "last_observed": 157.98, "last_observed_date": "2026-05-07",
+ "status": "ok", "breach_date": null, "trail_pct": 20.0,
+ "re_entry_watch": false, "currency": "EUR"}
+```
+
+## Env-var overrides (test isolation)
+
+- `CORE_TRAIL_DB` — overrides `scripts.db.DB_PATH` for the
+  `_core_trail_db_path()` resolution. Pinned per-test by the autouse
+  `_isolated_dbs` fixture in `tests/conftest.py` (alongside Phase 1a's
+  `DCA_RESERVE_DB`).
+- `CORE_TRAIL_MARKDOWN` — overrides `<repo_root>/memory/CORE-TRAIL.md`
+  for the `_core_trail_markdown_path()` resolution. Used by the
+  subprocess CLI tests to redirect the rendered-markdown destination to
+  a tmp path.
+
+A unified `TRADING_DB` env var that supersedes both per-feature vars
+(`DCA_RESERVE_DB` + `CORE_TRAIL_DB`) is an explicit followup once
+#117/#118/#119 land and the pattern proves out.
+
+## Writer call sites (two; both call the `update` CLI)
+
+1. `.claude/commands/check-triggers.md` step 0 (local slash command).
+2. `routines/check-triggers-daily.md` `## Prompt` block step 3 (cloud
+   routine on claude.ai).
+
+**Critical:** the cloud routine prompt is **manually synced** to
+claude.ai — repo merge does NOT auto-deploy it. After any change to the
+routine prompt block, the operator must push the new prompt to the live
+`check-triggers-daily` routine in the claude.ai web UI. Until then, the
+cloud routine writes via the old code path and leaves DB + markdown
+inconsistent. See memory `project_cloud_routine_config_drift`.
+
+The slash command and cloud routine BOTH skip the `update` call and
+treat the position as "data unavailable" if `bash scripts/prices.sh
+{SYMBOL}` fails — DO NOT advance trail state on stale data.
+
+## Operator deploy after merging a core_trail-touching PR
+
+1. `python -m scripts.backfill_core_trail` — seeds new rows from
+   committed `memory/CORE-TRAIL.md`. Idempotent: existing-symbol rows
+   are reported as `unchanged`, never updated (hand-edited DB rows are
+   protected).
+2. Re-sync the claude.ai cloud-routine prompt to match the merged
+   `routines/check-triggers-daily.md` `## Prompt` block.
+
+## Common debugging questions
+
+| Symptom | Likely cause |
+|---|---|
+| `memory/CORE-TRAIL.md` doesn't reflect the latest trail update | Operator hand-edited the rendered file; the next `update` CLI call will overwrite their edits. The markdown is a rendered view since #116 — they must call `update --symbol ... --close ...` instead |
+| Row count in `core_trail` is 0 after merge | Operator skipped the post-merge `python -m scripts.backfill_core_trail` step |
+| `core_trail` row's `last_observed_date` is yesterday's date despite a /check-triggers run today | Yahoo price fetch failed today; the routine correctly skipped the update. Re-run /check-triggers when the price source is back |
+| `breach_date` is set but `re_entry_watch` is false | Operator cleared `re_entry_watch` after the breach (re-bought or explicitly cleared). `breach_date` is history-preserving and stays set |
+| Dashboard pie classifies a held core ETF as satellite | `memory_files.core_tickers()` returns the bare symbol stripped of suffix; verify the `core_trail` row's `symbol` carries the right suffix (e.g. `VWCE.DE`) |
+| `render` output doesn't match committed `memory/CORE-TRAIL.md` byte-for-byte | Someone hand-edited the markdown. Restore by `python3 -m scripts.core_trail render --write` |
+| Migration regression test fails after schema change | Someone re-introduced an unconditional DROP inside `_SCHEMA_SQL`. The DROP must live in the guarded `_migrate_core_trail_to_v5` helper |
+
+## Related skills + sibling subsystems
+
+- `dashboard-maintenance` — covers the dashboard read path (`read_core_trail`, sleeve classification via `core_tickers()`).
+- `atr-stops-and-scaleout` — covers satellite stops (different mechanism: per-trade ATR-based, not per-ETF trail).
+- `execution-service-architecture`, `proposal-service-architecture`, `claude-runner-architecture` — sibling DB-canonical subsystems with the same pure-core / IO-edge split pattern.
+- (Followup: `reserve-ledger-architecture` skill should exist for Phase 1a's `reserve_ledger` + `scripts/dca_reserve.py` + `scripts/reserve_render.py` — gap from PR #137; tracking separately.)
