+# Phase 1b — migrate `memory/CORE-TRAIL.md` to `core_trail` table
+
+**Issue:** [#116](https://github.com/maxdimitrov/trading-bot/issues/116)
+**Parent epic:** [#113 — engine/operator split via DB-centric finish](https://github.com/maxdimitrov/trading-bot/issues/113)
+**Date:** 2026-05-24
+**Branch:** `feat/phase-1b-core-trail`
+**Base:** `main` @ `faebc2c` (Phase 1b #115 merge)
+**Status:** design approved, awaiting implementation plan
+
+## Problem
+
+`memory/CORE-TRAIL.md` is the canonical store of per-ETF trailing-stop state (ATH close, last observed close, trail percentage, breach flag, re-entry watch). It is mutated by **agent prose** inside `.claude/commands/check-triggers.md` (the local slash command) and `routines/check-triggers-daily.md` (the cloud routine prompt): the agent reads today's close via `bash scripts/prices.sh`, calls `scripts/core_trail.py`'s pure-function ratchet to compute new state, then **hand-edits the YAML block** under the per-ETF H2. The dashboard read path (`dashboard/api/app/data/memory_files.py:read_core_trail`) and sleeve classification (`dashboard/api/app/routes/allocation.py`) consume the markdown directly.
+
+`scripts/db.py` already contains `core_trail` table scaffolding (`symbol, ath_close, trail_pct, breached, updated_at`) and inert accessors (`get_trail`, `upsert_trail`, `TrailRow`). Nothing wires them up: the markdown is canonical, the table is empty in every running deployment, and the scaffolded schema is **missing six functional fields** that live in the markdown (`ath_close_date`, `last_observed`, `last_observed_date`, `breach_date`, `re_entry_watch`, and currency).
+
+Every trail update mutates the engine repo tree, which blocks the Phase 2 operator-dir extraction.
+
+## Goal
+
+After this PR:
+
+- The `core_trail` table is the canonical store of trailing-stop state.
+- `scripts/core_trail.py` (extended) owns DB read/write + render-on-demand alongside the existing pure-function ratchet.
+- The slash command (`.claude/commands/check-triggers.md`) and the cloud routine (`routines/check-triggers-daily.md`) call `python3 -m scripts.core_trail update ...` instead of hand-editing YAML.
+- `dashboard/api/app/data/memory_files.py:read_core_trail()` reads from DB; `allocation.py`'s sleeve classifier picks up the change transparently.
+- `memory/CORE-TRAIL.md` is a rendered artifact produced by `python3 -m scripts.core_trail render`.
+- Phase 1b children #117–#119 see one more datapoint for the migration template.
+
+## Non-goals
+
+- **Out of scope: relocating the rendered file** to `$ENGINE_OPERATOR_DIR`. That is Phase 2 (#120).
+- **Out of scope: changing the trail arithmetic.** The pure-function ratchet (`update_trail`, `breach_status`) is preserved verbatim.
+- **Out of scope: trail history.** The table stores current state only (single row per symbol), matching the markdown. A history table is not required by any consumer.
+- **Out of scope: surfacing the new `currency` column in the dashboard UI.** The column is added so the schema is self-describing and future-proofs a second core ETF on a non-Xetra venue. The dashboard `CoreTrailEntry` dataclass gains the field; no UI consumer exists yet.
+- **Out of scope: cloud-routine config push.** After merge, the operator manually re-syncs the live prompt on claude.ai per the existing convention (memory: `project_cloud_routine_config_drift`). The PR description carries the deploy note.
+
+## Design
+
+### Architecture — data flow before / after
+
+```
+BEFORE
+  /check-triggers (slash command, agent prose):
+    bash scripts/prices.sh VWCE.DE                 → today's close
+    python3 -c "from scripts.core_trail import …"  → compute new state
+    agent edits memory/CORE-TRAIL.md YAML inline   → write canonical
+
+  routines/check-triggers-daily.md cloud prompt    → same shape (mirror)
+
+  dashboard read:
+    memory_files.read_core_trail() ─reads─ memory/CORE-TRAIL.md
+    allocation.py.core_symbols() ─consumes─ symbols for sleeve classifier
+
+AFTER
+  /check-triggers (slash command, agent prose):
+    bash scripts/prices.sh VWCE.DE                 → today's close
+    python3 -m scripts.core_trail update \
+        --symbol VWCE.DE --close {C} \
+        --date {YYYY-MM-DD} --trail-pct ${CORE_TRAIL_PCT:-20}
+        → writes core_trail row (canonical)
+        → renders memory/CORE-TRAIL.md (derived)
+        → stdout: JSON {ath_close, last_observed, status, breach_date, …}
+        for the agent's report
+
+  routines/check-triggers-daily.md cloud prompt    → same CLI
+
+  dashboard read:
+    memory_files.read_core_trail() ─reads─ core_trail rows via db.connect()
+    allocation.py.core_symbols() ─unchanged consumer─
+```
+
+### Locked decisions
+
+| Decision | Value |
+|---|---|
+| I/O home | extend `scripts/core_trail.py` (pure fns stay; add DB I/O + render in the same module) |
+| Writer invocation | `python3 -m scripts.core_trail update --symbol SYM --close N --date YYYY-MM-DD --trail-pct N` |
+| Render invocation | `python3 -m scripts.core_trail render` (stdout) or `--write` (writes `memory/CORE-TRAIL.md`) |
+| Schema columns | inputs only — `symbol PK, ath_close, ath_close_date, last_observed, last_observed_date, trail_pct, breach_date NULL, re_entry_watch, currency, updated_at` |
+| Derived fields | `stop` and `status` recomputed by the renderer + the `update` CLI's stdout JSON |
+| Existing partial table | redefined cleanly (no live callers). `_SCHEMA_SQL` declares the v5 shape with `CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS`; a one-time guarded helper `_migrate_core_trail_to_v5(conn)` detects the v4 `breached` column and rebuilds the table. Bumps `SCHEMA_VERSION` to 5; drops the inert `upsert_trail` / `get_trail` / `TrailRow` from `db.py`. Critical: the DROP must NEVER live in `_SCHEMA_SQL` — `executescript()` would wipe data on every reopen. |
+| Currency | native value (EUR for VWCE.DE) + new `currency TEXT NOT NULL` column |
+| Backfill | `scripts/backfill_core_trail.py` — idempotent, audit-trail, lives in repo |
+| Test isolation | extend `tests/conftest.py` autouse fixture to also pin `CORE_TRAIL_DB`; `scripts.core_trail` reads it as the DB path override |
+
+### Six-step migration template (mirrors Phase 1a; deviation in step 5)
+
+| # | Step | Files | Commit prefix |
+|---|---|---|---|
+| 1 | Schema delta + version bump | `scripts/db.py` | `feat(db): redefine core_trail table for full markdown shape` |
+| 2 | Backfill | `scripts/backfill_core_trail.py` + tests | `feat(scripts): one-shot core_trail backfill from markdown` |
+| 3 | DB+render shim in `scripts/core_trail.py` | `scripts/core_trail.py` + `tests/conftest.py` + tests | `feat(core_trail): route writes through DB + render markdown` |
+| 4 | Dashboard read-cutover | `dashboard/api/app/data/memory_files.py` + tests | `feat(dashboard): read core_trail from DB` |
+| 5 | Agent-prose rewire + declarative cutover | `.claude/commands/check-triggers.md` + `routines/check-triggers-daily.md` + module docstrings | `chore(core_trail): declare markdown derived, DB canonical` |
+| 6 | Render-on-demand + rendered cutover | `scripts/core_trail.py` (CLI subcommand `render`) + `memory/CORE-TRAIL.md` replaced with rendered output | `feat(core_trail): render CLI + cutover rendered markdown` |
+
+**Deviation note for the PR description.** Phase 1a's step 5 was purely declarative (intro-text + docstring). For #116 step 5 also rewires `.claude/commands/check-triggers.md` and `routines/check-triggers-daily.md` from "agent edits YAML inline" to "agent calls `python3 -m scripts.core_trail update ...`". This is unavoidable because the pre-migration writer was agent prose, not Python; the rewire IS the write-cutover. The commit message acknowledges the deviation and Phase 1b reviewers can cite this spec section.
+
+### Step 1 — schema delta
+
+```sql
+-- _SCHEMA_SQL block: declares the v5 shape with IF NOT EXISTS so the
+-- string is safe to re-run on every connect() (executescript() does
+-- exactly that). The old v4 5-col scaffold, if present, is NOT touched
+-- here -- _migrate_core_trail_to_v5() handles that case once, post-
+-- _SCHEMA_SQL, in connect().
+CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS core_trail (
+    symbol TEXT PRIMARY KEY,
+    ath_close REAL NOT NULL,
+    ath_close_date TEXT NOT NULL,            -- 'YYYY-MM-DD'
+    last_observed REAL NOT NULL,
+    last_observed_date TEXT NOT NULL,
+    trail_pct REAL NOT NULL,
+    breach_date TEXT,                         -- NULL = not breached
+    re_entry_watch INTEGER NOT NULL DEFAULT 0,
+    currency TEXT NOT NULL,                   -- 'EUR', 'USD', ...
+    updated_at TEXT NOT NULL
+);
+```
+
+One-time migration helper (runs in `connect()` after `executescript(_SCHEMA_SQL)`, before the `_ensure_column` block):
+
+```python
+def _migrate_core_trail_to_v5(conn: sqlite3.Connection) -> None:
+    """Rebuild the inert v4 5-col core_trail scaffold to the v5 10-col
+    shape. Idempotent: detects v4 by the `breached` column; no-op on a
+    fresh DB (where _SCHEMA_SQL already created v5) or a v5 DB."""
+    cols = {r["name"] for r in conn.execute("PRAGMA table_info(core_trail)")}
+    if not cols or "breached" not in cols:
+        return
+    conn.execute("DROP TABLE core_trail")
+    conn.execute("CREATE TABLE core_trail (... v5 10-col DDL ...)")
+```
+
+Bump `SCHEMA_VERSION` from 4 to 5. Drop `get_trail`, `upsert_trail`, and the `TrailRow` dataclass from `scripts/db.py` (inert; replaced by typed reads/writes in `scripts/core_trail.py` that call `db.connect()` directly).
+
+**Critical invariant.** The DROP must NEVER live inside `_SCHEMA_SQL` — `executescript()` runs that on every `connect()` and would wipe Task 2's backfilled rows on every reopen. `tests/test_db.py:test_core_trail_v4_to_v5_migration_is_idempotent` is the regression guard.
+
+### Step 2 — backfill
+
+`scripts/backfill_core_trail.py`:
+
+- Reads `memory/CORE-TRAIL.md`.
+- For each `## SYMBOL` H2 section (skipping `Per-ETF format` and `Behavior` schema/notes sections), parses the fenced ```yaml block.
+- Infers `currency` per-symbol: heuristic = `'EUR'` for any symbol whose suffix matches `.DE|.AS|.MI|.PA|.L|.SW`, `'USD'` otherwise. Single-symbol scope today (VWCE.DE → EUR); the heuristic is in place for #117/#118 future-proofing.
+- `INSERT INTO core_trail (...) VALUES (...) ON CONFLICT(symbol) DO UPDATE SET ...` — idempotent re-runs replace fields with what's in the markdown.
+- CLI:
+
+  ```bash
+  python -m scripts.backfill_core_trail               # all symbols
+  python -m scripts.backfill_core_trail --symbol VWCE.DE --dry-run
+  ```
+
+- Lives in the repo as the audit-trail of how the DB was seeded.
+
+### Step 3 — DB + render shim in `scripts/core_trail.py`
+
+`scripts/core_trail.py` gains:
+
+- `_core_trail_db_path() -> str | None` — reads `os.environ.get("CORE_TRAIL_DB")`, falls back to `db.DB_PATH`. Matches the Phase 1a `_reserve_db_path()` shape.
+- `@dataclass(frozen=True) class CoreTrailRow` — the full 10-field projection.
+- `read_state(conn, symbol) -> CoreTrailRow | None`.
+- `write_state(conn, *, symbol, ath_close, ath_close_date, last_observed, last_observed_date, trail_pct, breach_date, re_entry_watch, currency) -> CoreTrailRow` — single-statement upsert inside `with conn:`.
+- `update_state(conn, *, symbol, current_close, observed_date, trail_pct, currency=None) -> CoreTrailRow` — orchestrator: reads existing row (or seeds a fresh one with `current_close` as the initial ATH if absent), applies the pure-fn `update_trail`, computes `breach_status`, flips `breach_date` on transition into `'breached'`, leaves `breach_date` set on subsequent `'breached'` observations (history-preserving), keeps `re_entry_watch` from the existing row (an operator-managed flag, never auto-cleared here). Returns the new persisted row.
+- `render(conn) -> str` — renders the canonical markdown view (template locked in §Step 6). Defined here, in step 3, because the dual-write shim needs to re-render the markdown after every DB write. Step 6 adds the CLI wrapper and the rendered-markdown cutover commit.
+- `render_to(conn, path) -> None` — writes `render(conn)` to `path`, UTF-8, LF line endings.
+- `update_cli(args)` — argparse subcommand. Required: `--symbol`, `--close`, `--date`, `--trail-pct`. Optional: `--currency` (defaults to existing row's value, or the backfill heuristic if seeding a new row). Calls `db.connect()`, calls `update_state`, calls `render_to(conn, repo_root / "memory" / "CORE-TRAIL.md")`, prints the new state as JSON on stdout.
+
+Add `CORE_TRAIL_DB` env var to the autouse fixture in `tests/conftest.py`:
+
+```python
+@pytest.fixture(autouse=True)
+def _isolated_dbs(tmp_path, monkeypatch):
+    monkeypatch.setenv("DCA_RESERVE_DB", str(tmp_path / "reserve.db"))
+    monkeypatch.setenv("CORE_TRAIL_DB", str(tmp_path / "core_trail.db"))
+```
+
+(Two env vars pointing at separate tmp DBs is fine even though both write to the same logical `trading.db` in production — tests don't need shared state across these paths. A unified `TRADING_DB` env var is a small followup once #117/#118 land and the pattern proves out.)
+
+### Step 4 — dashboard read-cutover
+
+`dashboard/api/app/data/memory_files.py:read_core_trail()`:
+
+```python
+# BEFORE
+def read_core_trail() -> list[CoreTrailEntry]:
+    path = _memory_dir() / "CORE-TRAIL.md"
+    if not path.exists():
+        return []
+    text = path.read_text(encoding="utf-8")
+    # ... regex+yaml.safe_load over H2 sections ...
+    return entries
+
+# AFTER
+def read_core_trail() -> list[CoreTrailEntry]:
+    from scripts.db import connect
+    from scripts.core_trail import TrailState, breach_status
+    with connect() as conn:
+        rows = conn.execute(
+            "SELECT symbol, ath_close, ath_close_date, last_observed,"
+            " last_observed_date, trail_pct, breach_date, re_entry_watch,"
+            " currency FROM core_trail ORDER BY symbol"
+        ).fetchall()
+    out: list[CoreTrailEntry] = []
+    for r in rows:
+        ath = float(r["ath_close"])
+        last = float(r["last_observed"])
+        pct = float(r["trail_pct"])
+        stop = ath * (1.0 - pct / 100.0)
+        status = breach_status(TrailState(ath_close=ath, stop=stop, last_observed=last))
+        out.append(CoreTrailEntry(
+            symbol=r["symbol"],
+            ath_close=ath,
+            ath_close_date=r["ath_close_date"],
+            stop=stop,
+            last_observed=last,
+            last_observed_date=r["last_observed_date"],
+            status=status,
+            trail_pct=pct,
+            re_entry_watch=bool(r["re_entry_watch"]),
+        ))
+    return out
+```
+
+`CoreTrailEntry` gains an optional `currency: str | None = None` field (additive; existing call sites unaffected). Derived `stop` and `status` are computed via the canonical `scripts.core_trail.breach_status` pure function — no duplicated logic in the dashboard layer.
+
+`core_symbols()` is unchanged — still calls `read_core_trail()` and strips the suffix.
+
+### Step 5 — agent-prose rewire + declarative cutover
+
+`.claude/commands/check-triggers.md` step 0 ("Core trailing-stop check"):
+
+```
+BEFORE (excerpt):
+   - Fetch today's close: `bash scripts/prices.sh {SYMBOL}` ...
+   - Read `CORE_TRAIL_PCT` from `.env` (default 20).
+   - Compute the new state via the pure-function module:
+
+     python3 -c "
+     from scripts.core_trail import TrailState, update_trail, breach_status
+     # parse the YAML block for this ETF, compute, print as YAML
+     ..."
+
+   - Write the new state back into the ETF's section.
+
+AFTER (excerpt):
+   - Fetch today's close: `bash scripts/prices.sh {SYMBOL}` → ${CLOSE}
+   - Update trail state (writes core_trail row + re-renders memory/CORE-TRAIL.md):
+
+     python3 -m scripts.core_trail update \
+         --symbol {SYMBOL} --close ${CLOSE} \
+         --date $(date -u +%F) --trail-pct ${CORE_TRAIL_PCT:-20}
+
+     stdout is the new state JSON: {ath_close, last_observed, status,
+     breach_date, ...} — use it for the report and the notify path.
+```
+
+`routines/check-triggers-daily.md` `## Prompt` block — same rewrite in the cloud-routine prompt verbatim. Plus a new line near the top of the prompt:
+
+```
+**Note: as of YYYY-MM-DD, memory/CORE-TRAIL.md is derived from the
+core_trail table. Do NOT hand-edit the YAML; call the CLI above.**
+```
+
+`memory/CORE-TRAIL.md` intro paragraph flips to declare DB canonical / markdown derived (becomes the renderer's intro template in step 6).
+
+`scripts/core_trail.py` module docstring flips: "State persisted in `core_trail` table; markdown rendered on demand."
+
+No code change in this commit beyond the docstring flip — the agent-prose edits and the docstring edit are the cutover artifact. Backfill from step 2 must have been run on the operator's DB before this commit lands so the DB is the canonical source by the time the prose rewires to call the CLI. The PR description carries the operator deploy steps:
+
+1. `python -m scripts.backfill_core_trail` (seed DB from current markdown)
+2. Merge PR
+3. Re-sync claude.ai cloud-routine prompt to match `routines/check-triggers-daily.md`
